# Kling Video Generation (fal.ai)

## API Details
- Provider: fal.ai (`@fal-ai/client`)
- Model: `fal-ai/kling-video/o3/standard/reference-to-video`
- Auth: `FAL_KEY` env var, configured server-side via `fal.config({ credentials })`

## Request Shape
```typescript
fal.queue.submit(MODEL_ID, {
  input: {
    start_image_url: string,    // first selected image — the opening frame
    prompt: string,             // fashion walk prompt with @Element1/2/3 refs
    elements: [                 // all selected images as reference elements
      { frontal_image_url: string }
    ],
    duration: "10",             // 10-second video
    generate_audio: false,
    negative_prompt: "blur, distort, low quality, deformed, static, frozen, jerky motion"
  }
})
```

## Polling
- Use `fal.queue.status(MODEL_ID, { requestId })` to poll
- Statuses: `IN_QUEUE` → `IN_PROGRESS` → `COMPLETED` | `FAILED`
- On `COMPLETED`, call `fal.queue.result(MODEL_ID, { requestId })` to get `result.data.video.url`
- Client polls `/api/video-status` every 5 seconds

## Image Selection Rules
- First selected image = `start_image_url` (the opening frame)
- All selected images (including first) become `elements`
- Default selection: first 3 gallery images in order
- User can toggle selection before generating
